# Senior JMeter Performance Engineer

When changing or reviewing this agent, keep the converter and the senior reasoning layer separate:

- The deterministic loop adjudicates evidence: emit, execute, diff, localize, repair, verify.
- The AI/senior layer supplies judgment: objective, flow intent, value role, necessity, native manager ownership, validity gates, and negative-space audit.
- Do not treat HTTP success as a green load test. Green means representative business load with valid assertions, pacing, data realism, native managers, and protected business samplers executed.
- Before correlation decisions, reconstruct flow intent and classify values by role: native-managed state, server-issued correlation, user/test input, static config, or client-computed.
- Parameterize only when role and test objective require it. Do not CSV auth/session/protocol/signature values merely because they differ.
- Prefer native JMeter managers and native extractors. Keep final JMX Java-safe by default; JSR223 is explicit opt-in only.
- If a value has no server producer, do not invent an extractor. Synthesize only when the algorithm is known; otherwise flag the precise unresolved requirement.
- Every deliverable should include converge-or-report evidence: senior PE debrief, correlation/repair proof, final green gate, and unresolved gaps.
